law.text:
The board shall keep a record of its proceedings and a register of all applications for licensure. The register shall state the following:
Name, age, and residence of each applicant;
Date of the application;
Place of business of the applicant;
Education and other qualifications of the applicant;
Whether an examination was required;
Whether the applicant was rejected;
Whether a license was granted;
Date of the action of the board; and
Any other information that the board considers necessary.
